article.headline: Manhattan 52, Iona 39
article.story: NEW YORK -- Chris Smith scored 15 points and Manhattan applied a stifling defense to beat Iona 52-39 on Monday night. Darryl Crawford added 13 points and Laurence Jolicoeur had 11 for the Jaspers (14-10, 8-6 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), who have won three in a row. Scott Machado scored 13 points and Gary Springer had 10 for the Gaels (11-14, 6-8), who have lost four of five. The game was the second-lowest MAAC scoring total by both teams since the league began in 1980. The only lower total was on Feb. 23, 1982, when St. Peter's defeated Manhattan 44-36. The points were the sixth-fewest in a game for Iona since the school began playing basketball in 1945. The 39 points were the fewest given up by Manhattan since defeating NJIT 70-28 at the outset of the 2007-08 season. Manhattan led 19-11 at halftime and never trailed in the second half.
